Full SHA-256 of "abc" in Verbose. Combines all primitives (rotr32,
ch, maj, sigmas), K[i]/W[i] lookups via 64-way if/else helpers, and
a 64-iteration recursive compression loop.
sha256_abc() returns the first 32-bit word of SHA-256("abc").
Expected: 0xba7816bf = 3128432319, matching `echo -n abc | sha256sum`.
